# Metadata for 97-FEB-1
**Original location:** `More My Documents/wp/97/97-FEB-1`
**Date:** 1997
**Date confidence:** high
**Date source:** filename pattern: 97-

**Category:** essay-draft epistemology visibility-model kant exposure narrative practical-knowledge

**Abstract:**
Major essay dated February 12, 1997 described as "a condensation and reshaping of 96-SEP-2." Critiques the visual model of knowledge shared from sophists through Kant. Proposes "exposure" as alternative epistemological model where subject and object are mutually vulnerable agents-patients. Develops contrast between sensations, feelings, and emotions, arguing Kant ignores the third category. Advocates narrative and dramatic presence as preserving the structure of practical knowledge.

**AI Recommendation:** Revised/condensed version of 96-SEP-2; see also 97-FEB-1-1 variant.

